FBIS3-14232 "drnes057_l_94010" FBIS-NES-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Mar 1994 ISRAEL Closure Said To Remain in Effect Through 2 Apr TA2303163294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1600 23 Mar 94 TA2303163294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The closure on the territories will continue until after the Passover holiday [2 April], which begins on Saturday night [27 March]. Police Commissioner Rafi Peled told Qol Yisra'el that when the holiday ends, the security forces will reassess the situation. But in the meantime, he said, the closure has calmed things down in the territories. He said that when it is lifted, the security situation is expected to get worse, particularly in Jerusalem.
